  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-30 22:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Indicator Logging Bug: Deep Trace + Debug Deploy\n\n**Task:** Fix indicator logging bug \u2014 outcomes JSONL has zero indicator fields.\n\n**Investigation:**\n1. `_last_indicators` set at L556 in `should_trade()` \u2014 only on SUCCESS path\n2. `execute_trade()` reads it at L612 \u2014 should have fresh data\n3. `log_trade_outcome()` has two paths: `indicators` param \u2192 `_last_indicators` fallback\n4. Code flow is: `should_trade()` returns direction + sets `_last_indicators` \u2192 main loop calls `execute_trade()` \u2192 which reads `_last_indicators` \u2192 passes to `_check_outcome()` \u2192 which passes to `log_trade_outcome()`\n\n**Root cause still unclear.** Flow looks correct on paper. Possible causes:\n- Asyncio timing: `_last_indicators` gets overwritten by next cycle before `_check_outcome` runs\n- But we capture `dict(self._last_indicators)` as a snapshot \u2014 should be safe\n- Maybe `should_trade` actually throws before L556 on some edge case\n\n**Debug deployed:** Added explicit logging BEFORE `execute_trade()`:\n- `\ud83d\udccb PRE-EXECUTE indicators: [keys] obi=value` \u2192 confirms they exist\n- `\ud83d\udc1b BUG: _last_indicators missing/empty` \u2192 confirms they don't\n\nBot restarted 22:43. First real test at 11h tomorrow.\n\n## 2026-03-30 22:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] MEMORY.md End-of-Day Update\n\n**Task:** Evening report window (22:00-23:00 UTC per AGENTS.md). Update MEMORY.md with all Day 1 learnings.\n\n**MEMORY.md updates made:**\n1. HL positions: ETH flipped LONG\u2192SHORT mid-day, net uPnL +$0.58\n2. W14 Day 1 FINAL: 7 trades, 5W",
